HEADWORD: finger cot
<hw>finger cot</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a close-fitting sheath worn at
the end of a finger, for protection of the finger or to avoid soiling
the object touched.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fingerstall, cot{3}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

